title: 2 pilots killed after colliding upon landing at National Championship Air Races
description: Two pilots were killed Sunday after their planes collided while landing at the National Championship Air Races in Reno, Nevada, the Reno Air Racing Association said.

title: Landslide in northwest Congo kills at least 17 people after torrential rain
description: Authorities in northwestern Congo say torrential rain has caused a landslide that killed at least 17 people overnight

title: Road collision kills 4 Greek rescue workers dispatched to flood-stricken Libya
description: Libya' health minister says four Greek rescue workers dispatched to Libya following devastating flooding in the eastern city of Derna were killed in a road collision

title: Trump refuses to answer questions about Jan. 6 conduct but says he 'behaved so well'
description: In an NBC interview, Trump refused or avoided answering questions about his conduct on Jan. 6 -- but maintained that it was his decision to challenge the 2020 election

title: Private Louisiana zoo claims federal seizure of ailing giraffe wasn't justified
description: A private Louisiana zoo says that federal regulators overreached last week when they took away an ailing giraffe

title: Ukraine is the spotlight at UN leaders' gathering
description: The war in Ukraine and its visiting president take center stage at the United Nations this week

title: WATCH:  Beachgoers help stranded shark back into water at Florida beach
description: Several beachgoers worked together to help a stranded shark get back into the swim of things.

title: 2 charged with murder following death of 1-year-old at day care
description: Two people face multiple charges after a 1-year-old boy died and three other children were hospitalized after suspected opioid exposure at a day care.

title: AG sues hospital system over privacy of Ohio girl who traveled for abortion
description: Indiana’s attorney general has sued the state’s largest hospital system, claiming it violated patient privacy laws when a doctor publicly shared the story of an Ohio girl who traveled to Indiana for an abortion

title: WATCH:  Thick sea foam seen in Nova Scotia from post-tropical cyclone
description: Thick sea foam churned up by post-tropical cyclone Lee blanketed parts of Nova Scotia's Lawrencetown Beach on Saturday.

title: 14-year-old arrested in fatal shooting in Florida
description: Authorities in Florida have arrested a 14-year-old boy in connection with a shooting that left one victim dead and another in critical condition.

title: House GOP in 'civil war' over Biden impeachment, looming shutdown: Jeffries
description: House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries argued Sunday that House Republicans are in "civil war" amid the Biden impeachment probe and a looming government shutdown

title: First two cargo ships arrive in Ukrainian port after Russia's exit from grain deal
description: Two cargo ships have arrived in one of Ukraine’s ports this weekend, using a temporary Black Sea corridor established by the government

title: Dozens are injured at an Eritrean event in Germany, including 26 police officers
description: German police say dozens of people including at least 26 officers were injured during unrest at an Eritrean cultural festival in the southwestern city of Stuttgart

title: Los Angeles sheriff's deputy shot in patrol vehicle, office says
description: The deputy, whose name has not been released, had been "shot in his patrol car," law enforcement officials said.

title: WATCH:  Boaters get front-row seat to humpback whales feeding
description: WHALE OF A TIME: Lucky whale watchers had a front-row seat to a humpback whale pod's feeding time while out on the water off Provincetown, Massachusetts.

title: Auto workers' union calls talks with Ford productive as strike continues
description: The striking auto workers' union calls the latest talks reasonably productive.

title: Rolling Stone founder removed from Rock Hall leadership after controversial comments
description: He made comments that were seen as disparaging toward Black and female musicians

title: Small plane crashes in Brazil’s Amazon rainforest, killing all 14 people on board
description: Brazilian authorities say a small passenger plane has crashed in the Amazon rainforest, killing all 14 people on board

title: UAW president reacts to temporary layoffs of non-striking employees
description: The head of the United Auto Workers said plans to temporarily lay off non-striking employees "won't work," as the unprecedented strike hits day two.
